<TEXT>
the promise of a quick refund is prompting more 
and more americans to have their tax returns filed electronically 
leading the irs to hope that the paper return will soon become a 
thing of the past for millions 
through last week the internal revenue service had received 
510000 returns electronically almost as many as were filed in all 
of 1988 only 120000 electronic returns were filed during the 
comparable period last year the irs expects as many as 2 million by 
the time this years filing season ends on april 17 
electronic filing is available this year in 36 states but only to 
taxpayers who are expecting a refund and whose returns are prepared 
by a professional if you like you may avoid another bit of 
paperwork by having your refund deposited electronically into your 
bank account 
next year electronic filing will be available in all 50 states 
but if irs planners have their way that will be only the beginning 
they are researching the feasibility of 
allowing taxpayers who dont get refunds about 22 percent of 
all filers to file electronically they would pay the balance due 
with a credit card but that would require congressional approval 
permitting taxpayers to file directly from their home computer 
into the irs computer this would require perfection of computer 
software and a system of protecting the privacy of the electronic 
return 
an electronic return usually produces a refund check within about 
18 days compared with five or six weeks for a paper return the irs 
benefits too from fewer errors and less paperwork over 10 years 
the irs anticipates electronic filing will save 200 million in 
processing costs 
if 18 days is too long to wait for a refund many professional 
preparers are offering refundanticipation loans 
for example dollar dry dock bank of new york has a 40state 
network that produces a refund check within three to five days the 
return can be prepared by the taxpayer by dollar dry dock 
professionals or any preparer just filing the return not filling 
it out costs 45 
the bank sends a check for the refund to the taxpayer who in 
effect is getting an interestfree loan until the irs check arrives 
hampr block which prepares more tax returns than any other 
company offers refundanticipation loans at about 3000 of its 
7500 outlets most of the branches of jackson hewitt tax service 
another large franchise preparer offer the instant refund 
the irs said wednesday that it had received 241 million returns 
electronic and paper through last week compared with 235 
million during the same period in 1988 this represents a reversal 
of the trend of the last several years when the number of early 
filers dropped each year 
about 109 million returns are expected this year 
the irs had processed 105 million returns by last weekend an 11 
percent improvement over the 1988 pace of fewer than 95 million 
the number of refunds is up 97 percent this year from 38 
million to almost 42 million the refunds averaged 805 compared 
with 782 during the same period last year 
