here are the main events for the funeral of emperor 
hirohito friday thursday and friday est 
730 am 530 pm est thursday ceremony of farewell at 
imperial palace with imperial family relatives 
900 am 7 pm est coffin is placed in the hearse 
930 am 730 pm est procession by motorcade from palace 
to funeral site at shinjuku imperial gardens passing through front 
gates of parliament building along the way 
1015 am 815 pm est motorcade arrives at funeral site 
1031 am 831 pm est coffin moved from hearse to bier 
procession on foot to funeral hall 
1040 am 840 pm est procession arrives at funeral hall 
and drapes are closed to separate the hall from funeral guests 
assembled in two long tents facing the hall while the coffin is 
placed in the hall 
1053 am 853 pm est fortyseven minute imperial 
ceremony begins in which offerings of food and silk cloth are made 
to the late emperor his son and successor emperor akihito reads a 
eulogy 
1140 am 940 pm est offerings are removed and ceremony 
ends drapes are closed and religious decorations removed 
1158 am 958 pm est drapes open and chief cabinet 
secretary keizo obuchi announces start of 67minute state funeral 
and observance of silence for one minute prime minister noboru 
takeshita and others to read eulogies foreign dignitaries walk up 
individually to pay last respects 
131 pm 1131 pm est coffin is moved to hearse 
140 pm 1140 pm est motorcade leaves funeral site for 
imperial mauseleum in hachioji a western suburb of tokyo 
335 pm 135 am friday est procession arrives at 
mausoleum and after a ceremony the coffin is placed in the tomb 
the ceremony adjourns for three hours while the grave is closed 
720 pm 520 am est final ceremony is held with 
offerings of food ends at 850 pm 650 am est 
foreign dignitaries participate only in the ceremonies at 
shinjuku imperial gardens which last from 1015 am to 140 pm 
815 pm to 1130 pm est thursday 
