<TEXT>
aldo joseph jacuzzi the head of a 
family company whose whirlpool bath became a symbol of indulgence in 
the 1970s has died he was 67 
the chief product of the jacuzzi brothers inc became virtually 
synonymous with hot tubs jacuzzi is listed in websters new 
world dictionary and a symbol of the southern california lifestyle 
during the disco era and into the 80s 
in 1954 jacuzzi brothers developed a hydromassage unit to treat 
a relative who was an invalid this unit developed into the 
whirlpool that propelled hottub waters of the affluent around the 
world 
jacuzzi brothers was formed in 1915 when the family bought a 
machine shop its first major product was the toothpick 
propeller adapted for airplanes during world war i after developing 
the nations first cabinstyle monoplane in 1920 the company 
abandoned the aircraft business when a relative died testing an 
airplane the family then concentrated the development of the 
jacuzzi injector pump used to propel water in the whirlpool bath 
aldo jacuzzi joined the family company in berkeley calif in 
1939 he held several positions there until the international 
headquarters was moved to little rock ark in 1963 
jacuzzi was named vice president in charge of purchasing and held 
that post until 1970 when he was appointed chairman 
in 1979 the family sold the business to kidde inc of saddle 
brook nj which was acquired in 1987 by hanson industries the 
united states arm of a british corporation 
the little rock company continues to be operated under the name 
jacuzzi brothers 
jacuzzi who died tuesday is survived by his wife granuccia 
amadei jacuzzi and two sons the funeral is friday 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

