fawaz younis contends he led the hijacking of a 
jordanian airliner in june 1985 because his superiors in the shiite 
moslem militia ordered it but that may not be the key defense when 
he goes on trial friday 
the case is considered a landmark because younis was the first 
suspected terrorist arrested under the 1984 hostagetaking act 
which gives the united states jurisdiction outside its territorial 
boundaries when american citizens are taken hostage 
no one was killed in the 39hour hijacking of 72 passengers and 
crewmembers which ended when the airliner was returned to beirut 
the passengers and crew released and the boeing 727 blown up 
