washington is the latest blow for the group that has been 
struggling to finance restoration of the 63yearold vessel the 
yacht was to have been turned over to president bush in november 
the ship is sitting in drydock in norfolk va with the projects 
liabilities of nearly 10 million outweighting assets by more than 
38 million according to the suit 
the suit asks for the 23 million the bank lent to the 
presidential yacht trust as well as interest attorneys fees and 
punitive damages 
