<TEXT>
troops of an elite army 
battalion attacked a rebel field hospital killing 10 wounded 
guerrillas and medical workers the roman catholic churchs legal 
aid office said thursday 
it said two of the female victims a mexican doctor and a 
14yearold nurse were raped or molested before being killed in 
the feb 13 attack 
the office a highly respected human rights organization in el 
salvador sent church representatives and forensic specialists to 
exhume the bodies of the two women 
the doctors body bore 10 bullet wounds and the nurses body six 
and both bodies were severely bruised on the inner thighs and 
breasts according to the legal aid office report 
radio vencermos the guerrillas clandestine station reported on 
feb 15 that troops of the atlacatl battalion attacked and destroyed 
the field hospital two days earlier it said six people three 
medical workers and three wounded guerrillas were killed 
the army denied the guerrilla radio charge when it was contacted 
last week by the associated press 
both the legal aid office and the rebel radio said that among the 
victims were alejandra bravo betancourt a 35yearold mexican 
physician and rosibel dubon a 14yearold paramedical worker 
their bodies were exhumed and examined last friday by the legal aid 
office 
the alleged massacre took place outside the village of los 
encuentros near the sumpul river that forms el salvadors northern 
border with honduras the northern province of chalatenango where 
los encuentros is located is a stronghold of leftist rebels waging 
a 9yearold civil war against the usbacked government 
col ciro lopez roque military commander of chalatenango told 
journalists thursday there was no field hospital near los 
encuentros but he said atlacatl troopers killed several guerrillas 
including the mexican doctor in combat feb 13 
they were treating one wounded subversive said lopez roque 
but it was not a field hospital there wasnt even a hut there 
legal aid said extensive interviews with residents of the area 
indicated that in addition to the doctor and nurse five wounded 
guerrillas and three paramedics were killed in the atlacatl attack 
those bodies were buried in various remote spots in the rugged 
mountainous terrain and were not exhumed said the report 
the church office concluded that a field hospital was in fact 
installed near los encuentros it said atlacatl troops attacked 
and destroyed the field hospital and killed war wounded and the 
medical personnel present 
because the bodies of the two exhumed women were completely 
nude and both were bruised around the breasts and on the inside of 
the thighs rape or attempted rape is presumed the report said 
the church office called the attack a flagrant violation of 
the salvadoran constitution and of the 1949 geneva conventions to 
which el salvador is a signatory 
the alleged massacre took place 10 days after a visit to el 
salvador by vicepresident dan quayle quayle delivered what he 
called a very emphatic message to the effect that washington 
expected the salvadoran armed forces to improve their record on 
respect for human rights 
