battle as a sign of any refusal by congressional democrats to seek 
bipartisanship consensus on the various issues 
the president believes the candidate deserves to have a 
hearing before the full senate he said lets hear what it is 
that theyre basing their judgment on 
weve been lobbying through the day the nomination went up we 
believe he will be confirmed and we will certainly work toward that 
end fitzwater said 
we dont believe this speaks to any larger question of 
bipartisanship he added saying that i would think the members 
of the senate and house would tell you the same thing this is 
quite a separate matter that has to be considered in that context 
fitzwater said the white house had been in the game since the 
