friday the day of emperor hirohitos funeral 
the liberal daily asahi shimbun wrote 
at the time hirohito ascended the throne six decades ago japan 
was regarded with suspicion by the world as an emerging military 
power we must never forget the tragic sacrifices that many 
people were forced to make in japan as well as abroad along 
japans path of change 
we must not turn our eyes away from this somber history it is 
most important to renew our awareness of the responsibilities japan 
has to the world today 
for todays state funeral ceremonies the government never 
really drew a clear line between the secular and the religious 
moreover the japanese public at large tends to bow to orders from 
above as a matter of course a perfect case in point is the 
