a series of explosions blew the roof off a 
building in an explosives plant complex thursday rocking homes more 
than a mile away and injuring at least five people authorities said 
fire raced through the building at jet research center inc a 
manufacturer of explosives for oil production triggering the 
explosions around 2 pm said police in this community of 3000 
an employee corine hines said the fire began when a mixture of 
chemical powders she was mixing in a jar ignited it just blew up 
in my face ms hines told wfaatv i couldnt run because i 
couldnt see 
two other jet research buildings containing explosives were 
untouched by fire and appeared to be safe several hours after the 
blaze said johnson county sheriff eddy boggs 
firefighters ran out of water about a halfhour after they began 
battling the fire and decided to let it burn itself out 
police asked news helicopters to stay away dispatcher billye 
lane said about an hour after the blast theyre expecting it to 
blow again lane said 
the explosion shook my house said jack hillis who lives 1 
miles from the plant 
boggs said he did not know how many people were in the building 
but about 50 jet research employees fled the complex witnesses said 
four people were taken by ambulance to huguley memorial hospital 
