<TEXT>
the most frustrating part of driving a 1989 acura integra is the 
other cars on the road many dont have anywhere near the 
performance and handling features of the integra and seem well to 
get in the way 
its not that the integra purposely wants to show off its just 
built to be a serious traveler 
introduced in late 1986 the car was named in january 1987 one of 
car and driver magazines 10 best it also was runnerup to its own 
kin the more expensive acura legend coupe in the competition for 
motor trends import car of the year 
in january 1988 the integra bowed again on car and drivers 10 
best list and in the annual car book released last december 
198688 integras had the honor of showing no owner complaints of 
trouble in federal government files 
not bad for a car that starts at 11260 but offers the 
performance of some higherpriced autos car and driver once wrote 
that the integras sticker price brings tears to the eyes of general 
motors executives 
it also brings out relatively wellheeled buyers many of whom 
were previous or current honda buyers integra sales in calendar 
1988 totaled more than 54000 up from more than 50000 in calendar 
1987 
median household income of integra fivedoor buyers is 54000 
said company spokesman mike spencer seventypercent are men 89 
percent have college education the median age is 39 and 78 percent 
are married 
its positioned as a family sports sedan spencer said noting 
the integra made by honda but sold in separate acura dealerships 
competes against the sporty honda prelude and widely popular 
honda accord 
but the integra leans more heavily toward the sports side than 
the family side spencer admitted saying the company has pushed 
the performance image and the ties to formula one racing with the 
car some engineered items such as the integras sophisticated 
electronic engine management systems stem from that racing 
experience the company says 
in contrast the accord appears a more sedate type of family 
vehicle although its 2liter 12valve fourcylinder engine is no 
slouch it compares with the integras 16liter 16valve twin 
overhead cam four cylinder and the preludes 2liter 16valve 
powerplant 
there are subtle differences among the cars spencer explained 
noting the prelude is positioned more as a sheer sports car with 
less interior room for passengers and cargo than the integra has 
pricewise the integra is amid its honda cousins the accord 
starts at around 11000 and the prelude begins at around 14000 
the test car an integra ls fivedoor squealed its tires a few 
times until i got accustomed to the 118 horsepower under the hood 
the integra sure tried to grab the road even in slick conditions 
the ride was all sport no cushiony floating feeling here but 
it also made for good road handling and feel 
seats were nicely contoured to fit the body well and not quite as 
fitted and low to the floor as those in the prelude making entry 
and exit easier 
the ride combined with the smooth enginefivespeed manual 
transmission performance and low road noise made for pleasurable 
traveling up front 
in the back seat legroom could be at a premium if the front 
seats were pushed back all the way rear legroom was ok if the front 
seats were pushed up a ways it also could be a close fit for three 
adults in the back seat 
in comparison the accord is a couple inches wider 
like nearly all family cars now the integras back doors had 
childproof locks and the rear power windows could be deactivated 
by a switch on the driver door 
the hatchback area was roomy and the rear seats could fold down 
for more room there was a shelf behind the rear seat where items 
could be placed it doubled as a partial cover for things stowed 
below in the hatchback and folded upward for access below 
i found i had to be sure to keep the rear lap belts out of the 
way when putting the rear seats back up or the belts could get stuck 
against the car body 
the integras fit and finish inside and out was impeccable i 
noted that while the integra had power windows and door locks the 
outside mirrors had to be adjusted manually as did the radio antenna 
consumer reports magazine ranked the 198687 integras much better 
than average according to its survey of owner trouble reports 
