there were eight selling days during the period this year and 
nine last year so percentage changes in sales are based on a daily 
selling rate rather than on total sales 
the overall sales rate during the period was bolstered by a 54 
percent increase in truck sales which offset a 03 percent decline 
in car sales 
sales during the first six weeks of last year were heavily 
influenced by buyer incentives offered by the automakers incentives 
including cash rebates and low financing deals were offered this 
year for a narrower range of cars and trucks 
for the year to date car and truck sales by domestic producers 
fell 32 percent to an average daily rate of 32334 compared with 
33412 last year there were 42 selling days between jan 1 and feb 
20 this year one fewer than during the same time last year 
the daily sales rate for cars was down 63 percent during the 
period while truck sales were up 15 percent 
chrysler corp midfebruary car sales fell 185 percent from the 
